name: Mallari, R. Peter
title: Attorney
notes: Ruben Peter Mallari, California State Bar license #206496. Historical residences in San Francisco, Redwood City, Atherton, Davis, and Sebastopol, CA.

name: Manseau, Robert B.
title: President / Founder
notes: Founder and President of First Rate Mortgage, Fremont, California, since 1993. Previously Loan Officer at San Mateo Credit Union.

name: Maslin, Philip Star II
title: Senior Design Sales Associate
notes: Resident of Belvedere Tiburon, CA. Attended University of California, Berkeley. Active in local railroad history and Landmarks Society.

name: McCubbrey, J. Bruce
title: Counsel, Intellectual Property
ngos: American Himalayan Foundation (Patent Lawyer on team)
notes: James Bruce McCubbrey, California State Bar license #38817. B.S.E. (1958) and J.D. (1961) from University of Michigan. Admitted California bar 1963; registered to practice before U.S. Patent and Trademark Office. Author and speaker on patent-antitrust law and biotechnology patents. Palo Alto, CA office.

name: McNabb, Mark Hopkins
title: Sound Department / Sound Mixer
notes: Film sound professional. Credits include Deep Impact (1998), Blast from the Past (1999), and The Glass House (2001).

name: Melvoin, Jeffrey D.
title: Television Writer-Producer / Showrunner
ngos: Writers Guild of America West (Board of Directors 2001-04; Founder and Chair, Showrunner Training Program and Writers Education Committee); Mystery Writers of America, Southern California Chapter (past board member)
notes: Harvard University magna cum laude 1975 (American history and literature). Former TIME magazine correspondent (1978-1982). Emmy Award winner for Northern Exposure (Outstanding Drama Series, 1992); two Golden Globe Awards; Television Critics Association Award; Mystery Writers of America Award. Executive Producer of Killing Eve, Designated Survivor, Army Wives, Alias, Picket Fences. Author of Running the Show: Television from the Inside (2023). Received WGA Morgan Cox Award 2015. Has taught at USC, UCLA, and Harvard.

name: Mosbacher, John (Jack) Ryan
title: Partner
ngos: Stanford Freeman Spogli Institute for International Studies (advisory council); Hoover Institution (NextGen Board); CalMatters (board member since 2023)
notes: Stanford University B.A. in Political Science with honors. Former research associate at Stanford's Freeman Spogli Institute (2012). Published in Foreign Affairs and The Washington Quarterly. Spent decade as touring musician, producer and professional theatre actor; toured with the band Train. Son of Stanford soccer player Bruce Mosbacher and 1988 U.S. Olympic marathoner Nancy Ditz. Watchfire Ventures is an early-stage venture capital firm founded 2020, based in Santa Barbara.

name: Moxley, Michael
title: Senior Vice President, Wealth Advisor / Co-founder, Moxley Kremer Group
notes: Co-founder of the Moxley Kremer Group at Morgan Stanley, San Francisco, CA. Group formed in 2003 serving affluent individuals and families. Holds Series 63 and Series 65 registrations. Registered in California and Texas.

name: Ogburn, David Wade
employer: BNY Wealth (formerly BNY Mellon Wealth Management)
title: Senior Client Strategist
ngos: Salvation Army of San Francisco (board member); Northern California Planned Giving Council (NCPGC) (board member); St. Anthony Foundation (Finance and Investment Committees); Salvation Army Western Territory (Finance and Investment Committees)
notes: Appointed Senior Client Strategist at BNY Mellon Wealth Management San Francisco June 2019. Previously Executive Director at JP Morgan Private Bank; roles at Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette, Credit Suisse, and Summitry. B.S. in Humanities and International Affairs from Georgetown University; MBA, Finance/Entrepreneurial Management from Wharton School, University of Pennsylvania. U.S. Navy veteran, six years active duty as Surface Warfare Officer. Resides in Alamo, CA.

name: Pagani, Sean-Paul A.
title: Principal, Enterprise Sales, Google Cloud
notes: Based in Concord, California. B.A. in Psychology from University of Rochester (1993-1997). Previously at Amazon Web Services, Oracle Corporation, VMware, and Dell Computers.

name: Parish, Jeffrey J.
employer: Jeffrey J. Parish Law Offices / Rosenblum, Parish & Isaacs PC
title: Attorney / President
notes: Born March 25, 1944, Sioux City, Iowa. B.A. from Yale University (1966); J.D. from Boalt Hall School of Law, UC Berkeley (1969). Admitted California bar 1970. Practice specializing in Securities Litigation, Unfair Competition, Real Estate, Intellectual Property, and Professional Liability in San Francisco, CA. Arbitrator since 1979.

name: Parnell, Aaron Lloyd Ulysses
title: Director / Reposturing Specialist
notes: Health and wellness professional based in San Mateo, California. Author of Living with Vitality: The Power of Extraordinary Health. Over 12 years in health and fitness industry. One of 35 massage professionals selected nationwide to serve as official masseur at the 1984 Los Angeles Olympics.

name: Paul, Jeffrey Frederic
title: REALTOR, Broker Associate, GRI
notes: DRE #01817414. Based in Mill Valley, CA (Marin County). Selling real estate since 2007; previously with Bradley Real Estate. Office at 800 Redwood Hwy, Suite 805, Mill Valley, CA 94941.

name: Poling, Drew
title: Director of Club and Custom
notes: Based in San Francisco, CA. B.S. in Marketing from Georgetown University (1986); Master of Music in Vocal Performance from University of Iowa (1997). Career in retail apparel spanning Bloomingdale's, UNICEF, Rowing Blazers, and J. Press. Previously Director of Club and Custom at Rowing Blazers.

name: Rosenberg, Stuart M.
title: Partner, Intellectual Property Litigation
notes: Palo Alto office. B.A. in Physics & Philosophy from Yale University (2002); J.D. with distinction from Stanford Law School (2005), Articles Editor for the Stanford Law Review. Law clerk to Chief Judge Paul R. Michel, U.S. Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit (2007-2008). Handles IP disputes at U.S. District Courts, USPTO, Federal Circuit, ITC. Recognized by Legal 500 USA for trade secrets work; named Litigator of the Week (Am Law Litigation Daily) for Fitbit ITC victory.

name: Salewski, Anthony I
title: Managing Partner
notes: Joined Genstar Capital in 2007; previously Chief of Staff at Barclays Global Investors (BGI) and Associate at Hellman & Friedman LLC; began career in investment banking at Morgan Stanley. MBA with distinction from Harvard Business School; B.A. with honors from Harvard College. Board director at Cetera Financial Group, GC Waves Holdings, GC Atlas Holdings, Orion Advisor Technology, and numerous other Genstar portfolio companies. San Francisco, CA.

name: Saltzer, David L
title: Chief Financial Officer
notes: Previously Accounting Manager at Kaiser Permanente. B.A. from University of California, Berkeley. Also operates David L. Saltzer CPA tax practice in Oakland, CA.

name: Schenkkan, Tex
employer: National Security Innovation Capital (NSIC) / Defense Innovation Unit (DoD)
title: Director
notes: Director of the National Security Innovation Capital (NSIC), a DoD program within the Defense Innovation Unit (DIU). NSIC was created by Congress in 2019 and launched February 2021 to fund early-stage dual-use hardware startups to protect against adversarial capital. Portfolio covers autonomy, communications, sensors, space, and power technologies.

name: Stegmiller, Kenneth Lawrence
title: Finance Consultant / Controller
notes: Certified Public Accountant with 19 years private industry and 5 years public accounting experience. Based in San Francisco, CA. Designed and built Koret Foundation's budgeting and forecasting model using Adaptive Insights. Previously at Zendesk, SquareTrade, and GreatSchools.

name: Stratmann, Erich W.
title: Music Editor
notes: Yale Drama School graduate (Sound & Music Design program). Career includes American Zoetrope, The Saul Zaentz Film Center, and Skywalker Sound. Film credits include Life of Pi (2012, Golden Reel Award winner for Best Sound Editing - Music in a Feature Film), Crazy Rich Asians, The Good Dinosaur, Rent (2005), I Am Number Four, Where the Crawdads Sing. LA-based music editor for 12+ years. Member of Motion Picture Sound Editors (MPSE).
